## Section Connecting to EC2 Instance - SSH via Command Line or Terminal
```
ssh ec2-user@ec2-13-52-102-83.us-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com #gives error

ssh -i ec2-course.pem ec2-user@ec2-13-52-102-83.us-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com
```

fix the uprotected private key file
chmod 0400 your_keypair_name.pem

verification:
 whoami
 ping google.com 

#Linux commands:
```
ls  #shows a list of directories or files
mkdir mydir # make a directory called mydir
cd .. #change directory
lsblk  #view your available disk devices and their mount points
lsblk -f
sudo file -s #get info about a specific device

```


